I used to live in SW Missouri myself, how has everything been there?
I'm south of you <@1279893710573932695> In SpringMo.

There always seems like there's building and expanding going on. What I call the suburbs of Springfield (Nixa, Ozark, Republic etc.) have been boom'n also! More migration here from other states as they're finding out their $$$ buys more here. Realtor friend has said that she's never seen so many million dollar homes go up and sell.
I'm glad that area is doing well, I always had a soft spot for Springfield. My former area hasn't been doing well due to a factory closure from what I read unfortunately. Within McDonald County.

Have you thought about moving back to the area? I mean, being from a neighboring state I found out that Missouri doesn't pay very well but the quality of life seems to be much better. We need more D's here! ü´è

Unfortunately not, as much as I agree that SW Missouri, as well as Missouri in general, needs a ton more democratic voters. But if I ever get the oppetunity hopefully I can do some online persuation within Missouri.
